# Project 4: Data Visualization (E-commerce Dataset)

## 📌 Objective
The goal of this project is to create meaningful visualizations from an e-commerce dataset to extract insights and present data in a clear and understandable way.

---

## 📊 Dataset Overview
- Total Records: 1200
- Total Columns: 14
- Type: E-commerce transactional data

---

## 🛠 Tools Used
- Python
- Pandas
- Matplotlib

---

## 📈 Visualizations Created

### 1. Product Distribution (Bar Chart)
- Shows frequency of each product sold.
- Helps identify best-selling products.

### 2. Order Status (Pie Chart)
- Displays proportion of different order statuses (Delivered, Cancelled, etc.).
- Helps understand order completion rate.

### 3. Referral Source Analysis (Bar/Pie Chart)
- Shows where customers are coming from (Instagram, Facebook, Email, etc.).

### 4. Items in Cart (Histogram)
- Shows distribution of number of items per order.
- Helps understand customer buying behavior.

### 5. Total Price Distribution (Histogram)
- Shows spending pattern of customers.
- Helps identify low, medium, and high-value purchases.

---

## 🔍 Key Insights
- Certain products dominate sales compared to others.
- Most orders fall under specific status categories.
- Social media platforms are major traffic sources.
- Customers mostly buy 5–7 items per order.
- Majority of customers fall in mid-range spending category.

---

## 🎯 Conclusion
This project demonstrates how data visualization helps convert raw data into meaningful insights for better business decision-making.

